{{define "content"}}
<nav class="cds-breadcrumb" aria-label="Breadcrumb"><a href="/admin/overview">Admin</a> / Backup &amp; restore</nav>
<h1 class="cds-h1">Backup &amp; restore</h1>
{{if .Error}}<div class="cds-inline-notification cds-inline-notification--error" role="alert">{{.Error}}</div>{{end}}
{{if .Available}}
<div class="cds-tile-grid">
  <section class="cds-tile">
    <div class="cds-metric__label">Node data directory</div>
    <div class="cds-metric__value cds-metric__value--small">{{.DataDir}}</div>
  </section>
  <section class="cds-tile">
    <div class="cds-metric__label">Main-vault logical live data</div>
    <div class="cds-metric__value">{{.Used}}</div>
  </section>
  <section class="cds-tile">
    <div class="cds-metric__label">Main-vault soft admission quota</div>
    <div class="cds-metric__value">{{.Quota}}</div>
  </section>
</div>
<h2 class="cds-h2">Consistent offline backup</h2>
<p class="cds-muted">The node broker and crawler frontier describe one crawl state. A consistent backup therefore stops the crawler before the node, archives both durable stores, and starts the node before the crawler, including after a failed copy. The archive contains the node vault and search index plus the crawler checkpoint and private peer identity; protect it accordingly. Secrets remain hashed. Docker uses separate node and crawler volumes, while systemd archives their shared data tree. Run one of these on the host, from the repository or package root:</p>
<h3 class="cds-h3">Docker deployment</h3>
<pre class="cds-code">{{.DockerBackup}}</pre>
<h3 class="cds-h3">systemd deployment</h3>
<pre class="cds-code">{{.SystemdBackup}}</pre>
<h2 class="cds-h2">Restore</h2>
<p class="cds-muted">A restore stops the crawler before the node, wipes the selected durable targets, restores the coordinated archive, and starts the node before the crawler. Verify node health and local search first, then confirm that the crawler reports frontier recovery without a checkpoint error.</p>
<h3 class="cds-h3">Docker deployment</h3>
<pre class="cds-code">{{.DockerRestore}}</pre>
<h3 class="cds-h3">systemd deployment</h3>
<pre class="cds-code">{{.SystemdRestore}}</pre>
<p class="cds-muted">The full procedure and cross-version compatibility notes live in <code>doc/backup-restore.md</code>.</p>
{{end}}
{{end}}
